&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an Undergraduate Coordinator in the Medical Education Centre at Withybush Hospital, Haverfordwest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have experience of working in a busy office environment, the ability to prioritise work, work on own initiative and have excellent communication skills, as well as the ability to be flexible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties to include being the first point of contact in dealing with all matters relating to medical student placements in Withybush Hospital from both Cardiff and Swansea Medical Schools; organising the various student timetables and Inductions, ensuring all Medical School Curriculum are provided to ensure a successful placement. Provide an administrative service to the Honorary Senior Lecturer and Medical Education Manager and provide pastoral support for all Medical Students and Physician Associate placements within Withybush Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries can be made to Rhiannon Davies, Medical Education Manager on (01437) 773753.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews for this post will be held on 25th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
